> Use this page to edit your rathole **client** config (`rathole.toml`) and to start or stop the rathole client.

<?
$file = "/boot/config/plugins/rathole/rathole.toml";
$text = file_exists($file) ? file_get_contents($file) : '';
$default_text = $text;
?>

<?
exec('ratholeorig --version 2>&1 | grep -Po "[\d]+\.[\d]+\.[\d]+"', $output);
$currentversion = isset($output[0]) ? $output[0] : 'unknown';
?>

<?
exec('pgrep -f "ratholeorig.*--client" 2>/dev/null', $pidout);
$running = !empty($pidout);
$statustext = $running ? '<span style="color:#5fba3a">&#9679; Running</span>' : '<span style="color:#e05c5c">&#9679; Stopped</span>';
?>

<html>
<head>
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
<style>
.row { display: flex; }
.column { padding: 10px; }
.left { flex: 1; }
.right { flex: 3; }
.btn { margin-right: 6px; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="row">
  <div class="column left">
    <?
    echo "Installed version: $currentversion";
    echo "<br><br>Status: $statustext";
    ?>
    <br><br>
    <form method="POST" action="/update.php" target="progressFrame">
      <input type="hidden" name="#include" value="/webGui/include/update.php">
      <input type="hidden" name="#command" value="/etc/rc.d/rc.rathole">
      <input type="hidden" name="#arg[1]" value="start">
      <input type="submit" class="btn" value="Start">
    </form>
    <br>
    <form method="POST" action="/update.php" target="progressFrame">
      <input type="hidden" name="#include" value="/webGui/include/update.php">
      <input type="hidden" name="#command" value="/etc/rc.d/rc.rathole">
      <input type="hidden" name="#arg[1]" value="stop">
      <input type="submit" class="btn" value="Stop">
    </form>
  </div>
  <div class="column right">
    <h2>Edit client config</h2>
    <form markdown="1" method="POST" action="/update.php" target="progressFrame">
      <input type="hidden" name="#include" value="/webGui/include/update.file.php">
      <input type="hidden" name="#file" value="<?=$file;?>">
      <textarea spellcheck="false" cols="80" rows="22" name="text" style="font-family:bitstream;width:100%"><?=$text;?></textarea>
      <br>
      <input type="submit" value="Apply"/><input type="button" value="Original" onclick="setDefault(this.form)">
    </form>
  </div>
</div>

</body>
</html>

<script>
function setDefault(form) {
  form.elements['text'].value = <?=json_encode($default_text);?>;
}
</script>

> Click the **Apply** button to save the current config to `/boot/config/plugins/rathole/rathole.toml`.
>
> Click the **Start** / **Stop** buttons to control the rathole client daemon.
